The paper deals with secure communications among smart devices, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a system model and consistent terminology for SDP schemes, which can be considered as a systematization effort (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of out-of-band channels and adversary models, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.NI). Finally, the paper analyzes the security weaknesses of existing SDP schemes, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
